---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About - txtui" description="About txtui - Plain text UI components for AI agents">
  <header class="mt-6 mb-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2">About</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="space-y-6 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      <strong>txtui</strong> is a catalog of plain text UI components designed for AI agents.
    </p>

    <p>
      When working with AI agents, sharing a visual image of a UI component can be difficult.
      txtui provides ready-to-copy text-based UI components that you can paste directly into
      your conversations with AI agents to quickly communicate your design intent.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Why txtui?</h2>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-text-muted">
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Copy & paste ready</span> — No AI generation wait time. Find the component you need and copy it instantly.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Component-based</span> — Individual UI parts like buttons, forms, and tables, not entire screen layouts.
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="text-text">Platform agnostic</span> — Unlike HTML/CSS or Tailwind catalogs, plain text works for web, mobile, games, and any other medium.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">How to use</h2>

    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-text-muted">
      <li><span class="text-text">Browse</span> the component catalog on the top page</li>
      <li><span class="text-text">Filter</span> by tags to find the component you need</li>
      <li><span class="text-text">Copy</span> the variation that matches your intent</li>
      <li><span class="text-text">Paste</span> it into your AI agent conversation</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
</Layout>
